# Life Assistant — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router), Vercel AI SDK 4.x, TypeScript strict
- MCP servers per domain (career, finance, fitness, hobbies)
- SQLite via better-sqlite3, Tailwind + shadcn/ui, Auth.js v5
- Turborepo monorepo, Vitest + React Testing Library

## TDD Workflow
- Write failing tests BEFORE implementation code
- MCP server tools first, then UI
- Run vitest after every change

## Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types
- Zod for all external input validation
- nanoid for all primary keys
- Parameterized SQL only — never template literal SQL
- Functions under 50 lines, files under 300 lines
- Immutable patterns: return new objects, never mutate arguments
- Structured logging via pino — no console.log
- Store prompt templates in prompts/ within each MCP server

## Model Routing
- Haiku 4.5: CRUD, tool calls, nudges, classification
- Sonnet 4.6: coaching, goal decomposition, cross-domain reasoning

## File Patterns
- apps/web/ — Next.js app (MCP host + UI)
- packages/mcp-{domain}/ — One MCP server per life domain
- packages/shared/ — Shared types, memory utils, privacy helpers
- Tests alongside source in each package
